  "description": [
    "JR s Jo 58 J o i 0 As it drew near the entrance the flfet slackened speed for it was thn near sundown All the ships were dark the decks cleared for action and the sharpest outlook kept in all direc tions The entranie to the harbor was thought by the Spaniards to be well defended and it would be so considered against anything but a fleet such as came there from Hongkong On the leftband side entering there are two batteries one on Point Mariveles and a smaller one further up the bay Ou the right hand side there are also two batteries one at Limbones point and aaothr at Restingo These last are on the Cavite side of the bay In the middle of the entrance are three is lands the largest of which is Carre quideo which was to have been forti fied but the Spaniards did not have land armament to spare It was un derstood that the entrance to the by as well as the bay itself was loaded with electric mines and torpedoes but if this was the case they did not ax plode for the American flet sailed ever and through them"
